Radioify Windows shell integration package
=========================================

This directory is generated by the build when
RADIOIFY_BUILD_WIN11_EXPLORER_INTEGRATION=ON.

Contents:
- radioify_explorer.dll: packaged IExplorerCommand adapter for folder targets
- Package.appxmanifest: MSIX manifest for Radioify file associations and Explorer context menu registration
- README.txt: generated notes for this package lane

Current status:
- The full MSIX package is the standard Windows install and shell integration path.
- File context-menu commands are registered declaratively through file associations.
- The Explorer command DLL is registered only for directories.
- Desktop background/null-selection menus are intentionally not registered.
- This directory is generated build output, not source-of-truth.

Useful commands:
- Build: .\build.ps1 -Static -Win11ExplorerIntegration
- Install: .\install_win11_explorer_integration.ps1
- Dry-run install: .\install_win11_explorer_integration.ps1 -WhatIf
- Uninstall: .\uninstall_win11_explorer_integration.ps1

MSIX output:
- The release packaging flow produces the signed .msix in the dist root.
- The package contains radioify.exe, radioify_explorer.dll, icons, visual assets,
  file association metadata, declarative file verbs, and directory command registration.
